# .cursorrules (catn8.us)

## Environment Information (Persistent)
- **Dev Site (Vite):** http://localhost:5178
- **Dev Site (Backend):** http://localhost:8888
- **Live Site:** https://catn8.us
- **Credentials:** Never store plaintext credentials in repo rules. Use `.env` and local secret stores only.

## Tech Stack
- PHP (API endpoints in `/api`, shared libraries in `/includes`)
- TypeScript + React (Vite-built frontend)
- JavaScript (tooling scripts)
- CSS (Vite-managed)

## Front-end / Build
- Vite `^7.x` (build output to `dist/`, manifest enabled)
- React `^18`
- React Router dependency is available if route-level React navigation is needed

## Server / Runtime
- Local development database is **MySQL**
- PHP endpoints should use centralized config/bootstrap files

## Security Baseline
- Every mutating endpoint must enforce explicit auth
- Mutating actions must use `POST`/`PUT`/`DELETE`, not `GET`
- Validate and normalize all external input at endpoint boundaries
- Parameterize all untrusted SQL values
- Never commit secrets or raw private keys

## Coding Guidelines
- Keep shared API/data interfaces in `src/types/`
- Avoid explicit `any` where practical
- Use semantic interactive HTML elements (`button`, `a`)
- Keep console/debug noise out of committed code

## Critical Constraints
- Use `src/core/ApiClient.ts` for frontend API requests
- Keep `index.html` as the frontend entry shell
- Do not add silent fallbacks that hide backend errors
